& [CombinedValidationCheckpointIntegrationDesign] is the design contract for reporting combined validation inside long-run checkpoints
  @ [created_at] 2026-05-30T13:18:00Z
  @ [governing_specification] specifications/Hierarchical_Agent_Swarm.sop
  @ [related_design] coordination/combined_artifact_validation_design.sop
  @ [harness_module] src/negotiated_agent/long_run.py
  @ [validation_module] src/negotiated_agent/artifact_validation.py

  + [design_status] is ready_for_implementation_slice
  + [authority_boundary] is checkpoint_validation_summary_not_acceptance_gate
  + [primary_goal] is make the long-run checkpoint report combined validation over the same dry-run manifest and Shaliach probe evidence it just produced
  + [non_goal] is validating a checkpoint file after it is written
  + [non_goal] is re-running validate-artifacts.ps1 from inside the harness
  + [non_goal] is approving generated code, Manager decisions, or target workspace mutation

& [RecursionBoundary] is the required implementation constraint
  + [rule] is harness must not depend on reading coordination/long_run_checkpoint.sop while building that same checkpoint
  + [rule] is combined validation should use the run_manifest.sop from the dry-run root parsed from dry_run stdout
  + [rule] is checkpoint probe validation should be built from the in-memory Shaliach probe CommandResult
  + [rule] is output may summarize combined validation status in LongRunCheckpoint after all source evidence exists in memory
  + [authority_boundary] is in_memory_summary_not_self_referential_checkpoint_read

& [CheckpointFields] is the intended checkpoint vocabulary
  + [field] is combined_artifact_validation_status
  + [field] is combined_artifact_validation_manifest_status
  + [field] is combined_artifact_validation_checkpoint_probe_status
  + [field] is combined_artifact_validation_authority_boundary
  + [authority_boundary] is validation_summary_not_final_acceptance

& [GatingPolicy] is the deterministic continuation rule
  + [rule] is combined validation passed may support ready_for_continuation
  + [rule] is combined validation failed should make checkpoint status needs_attention
  + [rule] is combined validation incomplete should make checkpoint status needs_attention when manifest validation was possible
  + [rule] is combined validation not_run is allowed only when dry-run root or run_manifest.sop cannot be found and should be reported explicitly
  + [authority_boundary] is continuation_readiness_not_human_approval

& [ProofExpectations] is the minimum implementation proof
  + [test_case] is checkpoint SOP records combined_artifact_validation_status passed for a valid dry-run manifest and passed Shaliach probe
  + [test_case] is checkpoint status needs_attention when combined validation fails because manifest refs are missing
  + [test_case] is checkpoint status needs_attention when combined validation is incomplete
  + [test_case] is combined validation not_run is reported when dry-run stdout lacks a run root
  + [test_case] is harness does not read coordination/long_run_checkpoint.sop while building the checkpoint
